proof.p:
Hence, with A = {a_1, a_2, ..., a_{|A|}}, breaking up the disjoint probabilities as above gives

	P(A) & = P( \{ a_1 \} \cup \{ a_2 \} \cup ... \cup \{ a_{|A|} \} )
	 & = P(\{ a_1 \}) + P(\{ a_2 \} ) + ... + P(\{ a_{|A|} \} )
	 & = \frac{1}{{|S|}} + \frac{1}{{|S|}} + ... + \frac{1}{{|S|}}
	 & = \frac{|A|}{{|S|}}

as desired.

